The only reason this place gets 4 stars is due to price.
The juices and elixers are delicious and do make you feel better.
Not going to lie, the elixers are awesome for hangovers, colds, and headaches.
I was not a believer in natural remedies such as oils and things but I'm starting to believe in it.
This place is on the side of true food and is around 5 bucks a drink.
The staff is super knowledgeable and many times speak over my head, which isn't too tough to do.
I definitely prefer this place to true food.

